\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 0. How to read this document\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 This PRD is co-authored. Sections marked **[CPO]** define *what* we are building and *why it wins*; sections marked **[CTO]** define *how* it is engineered, secured, and made extensible. Where the two intersect (data model, RBAC, integration seam) both signatures apply. V2 items are described as **roadmap**, never as scope \'97 they exist here only so the V1 architecture leaves the right seams.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 1. Executive summary [CPO + CTO]\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Debt Recovery OS is a B2B operating system for managing distressed-debt recovery, used by banks/MFOs, collection agencies, and legal firms in Uzbekistan. It is **not a CRM**. It is a recovery-infrastructure layer that manages the full lifecycle of a debt:\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 >\cf0 \strokec4  **Portfolio \uc0\u8594  Assignment \u8594  Collector activity \u8594  Legal prep \u8594  Court tracking \u8594  MIB tracking \u8594  Recovery / Closure**\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 The platform is a neutral **coordination, analytics and control layer** between bank, collector, legal firm, and (later) the state. It does not replace collectors, lawyers, or MIB (the state Bureau of Compulsory Enforcement). Private collectors and legal firms in Uzbekistan are not state enforcers \'97 they cannot freeze accounts, write off money, restrict travel, restrict property, or self-execute judgments. **The platform tracks and coordinates; enforcement stays with MIB.** Every product decision in this document respects that boundary.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 **V1 scope:** a private, multi-tenant platform connecting bank \uc0\u8596  collector \u8596  legal firm with realistic seeded data, role-aware workflows, and working state transitions \'97 with all in-app text in Russian and monetary values shown in USD (and UZS where a case amount is displayed). No government integration is built; the integration boundary exists with mock adapters only.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 2. Problem & opportunity [CPO]\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### 2.1 The problem today\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Banks and MFOs in Uzbekistan carry growing NPL (non-performing loan) portfolios and hand them to a fragmented network of collection agencies and legal firms. Coordination happens over spreadsheets, phone calls, and messenger chats. This creates four structural failures:\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 1. \cf0 \strokec4 **No single source of truth.** A debt's history lives in whoever last touched it. When a lawyer or collector leaves, institutional knowledge and metrics walk out the door.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 2. \cf0 \strokec4 **No accountability layer.** Banks cannot compare agencies objectively, cannot see where SLA is breached, and cannot audit who did what, when, and with what result.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 3. \cf0 \strokec4 **Data-quality rot.** Portfolios arrive with missing \uc0\u1055 \u1048 \u1053 \u1060 \u1051 , malformed amounts, and duplicates \'97 errors that surface only after weeks of wasted collection effort.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 4. \cf0 \strokec4 **Poor capital decisions.** Banks litigate debts that cost more to recover than they return, because nobody models expected recovery against cost-to-recover before filing.\cb1 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### 2.2 Why now\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Recovery is being professionalized and, increasingly, digitized (E-SUD e-courts, notary \uc0\u1080 \u1089 \u1087 \u1086 \u1083 \u1085 \u1080 \u1090 \u1077 \u1083 \u1100 \u1085 \u1072 \u1103  \u1085 \u1072 \u1076 \u1087 \u1080 \u1089 \u1100 , MIB enforcement). A neutral platform that sits *between* the parties \'97 owning the record, the workflow, and the analytics \'97 becomes the natural coordination layer as those state systems come online. **We win the private-coordination layer first (V1), then plug into the state systems as they mature (V2).**\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### 2.3 Positioning (must persist in UI copy)\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 The platform is a **neutral coordination, analytics and control layer**. It does not replace collectors, lawyers, or MIB.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 Never show a collector "freezing an account." Show them **recording a request** or **tracking a state action**.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 Tagline in header/footer: **\'ab\uc0\u1045 \u1076 \u1080 \u1085 \u1072 \u1103  \u1086 \u1087 \u1077 \u1088 \u1072 \u1094 \u1080 \u1086 \u1085 \u1085 \u1072 \u1103  \u1089 \u1080 \u1089 \u1090 \u1077 \u1084 \u1072  \u1074 \u1079 \u1099 \u1089 \u1082 \u1072 \u1085 \u1080 \u1103 \'bb.**\cb1 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ---\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
