\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 7. Architecture [CTO]\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### 7.1 Principles\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 1. \cf0 \strokec4 **Multi-tenant by organization.** Top-level tenant = a bank/MFO. Agencies and legal firms are connected participant orgs scoped to that tenant.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 2. \cf0 \strokec4 **Case as the central aggregate.** A Case has a debtor, amount, collateral flag, status, assigned org, event timeline, documents, payments, SLA timers, and a cost ledger.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 3. \cf0 \strokec4 **Event-sourced timeline / audit trail.** Every action writes an *immutable* event (who, what, when, result). This powers the audit log, the data-validation service, and agency analytics.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 4. \cf0 \strokec4 **Institutional identity, not personal.** Cases belong to the bank org, not to an individual lawyer's signature. A lawyer's \uc0\u1069 \u1062 \u1055  is an operational signing layer \'97 model \cf7 \strokec7 `signedBy`\cf0 \strokec4  as a removable operational attribute, never as the owner of the case. If a lawyer leaves, history and metrics persist on the org.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 5. \cf0 \strokec4 **Pluggable integration boundary.** A single \cf7 \strokec7 `IntegrationAdapter`\cf0 \strokec4  interface; V1 ships mock adapters only.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 6. \cf0 \strokec4 **RBAC enforced server-side.**\cb1 \
\
