\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 8. Key user flows (must be clickable end-to-end) [CPO]\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 Each flow writes audit events.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 1. \cf0 \strokec4 **Onboard a portfolio.** Bank Admin uploads Excel \uc0\u8594  validation report flags errors (missing \u1055 \u1048 \u1053 \u1060 \u1051 , bad amounts, duplicates) \u8594  fix/confirm \u8594  cases appear as *New* in the list and on the Control Tower.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 2. \cf0 \strokec4 **Assign & work a case.** Admin assigns a *New* case to an agency \uc0\u8594  Collector sees it \u8594  logs a *Promise to pay* with a date \uc0\u8594  status updates \u8594  timeline + SLA timer update \u8594  Control Tower reflects it.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 3. \cf0 \strokec4 **Escalate to legal & generate documents.** Case crosses 61 DPD or admin escalates \uc0\u8594  goes to Legal Firm \u8594  lawyer generates a court package (PDF preview) \u8594  status *Court package ready* \uc0\u8594  *Filed to court* (manual) \uc0\u8594  tracked to *Court decision received*.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 4. \cf0 \strokec4 **Enforcement routing decision.** On a case, choose notary (undisputed) vs court (disputed); platform records the path; both converge to a (mock) MIB view.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 5. \cf0 \strokec4 **Recover & close with approval chain.** Collector records full payment \uc0\u8594  initiates transfer \u8594  Manager approves \u8594  Accountant approves \u8594  case *Paid* \uc0\u8594  *Closed*. Every step audited.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 6. \cf0 \strokec4 **Decide with ROI.** Admin opens the Legal ROI Calculator on a high-value case \uc0\u8594  sees expected recovery < cost \u8594  recommendation to restructure \u8594  records *Restructuring proposed*.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 7. \cf0 \strokec4 **Compare agencies & reassign.** Admin opens Agency Analytics \uc0\u8594  sees an agency underperforming \u8594  reassigns its open cases via the marketplace \u8594  audit event written (with mandatory reason).\cb1 \
