\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## 11. Compliance, security & data localization [CTO]\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 **Immutable audit trail.** \cf7 \strokec7 `CaseEvent`\cf0 \strokec4  records are append-only. No update/delete path exists in the API. The audit log is filterable and exportable.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 **Data localization.** On-premise-capable deployment; object storage and DB run inside the bank's perimeter.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 **PII handling.** \uc0\u1055 \u1048 \u1053 \u1060 \u1051 , phone, address, and asset/account data are personal data \'97 access is role-scoped and every read of sensitive asset data is itself an audit event in production.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 **Institutional identity.** \cf7 \strokec7 `signedBy`\cf0 \strokec4  (\uc0\u1069 \u1062 \u1055 ) is an operational attribute on documents, removable without affecting case ownership or historical metrics.\cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 - \cf0 \strokec4 **Boundary integrity.** No code path lets a private participant perform a state enforcement action. The most a collector/lawyer can do is *record a request* or *track* an MIB action.\cb1 \
